none: Third collection of poems by an active participant in the liberation space, Sŏl Chŏng-sik (1912-1953), writing on the theme of nation-building which was the major concern for the writers of the liberation space. Sŏl majored in English Language and Literature in Mt. Union University in Ohio, and joined Choson Munhakka Tongmaeng while working for the US military in South Korea. He fled to North Korea during the Korean War and executed in 1953. The author of the modernist book cover and textual lay out is painter Pak Mun-wŏn.
